---
import ContentLayout from '../layouts/ContentLayout.astro';

const SITE = 'https://gokhangunduz.github.io/alpha';

const schema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'BreadcrumbList',
  itemListElement: [
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home',           item: `${SITE}/` },
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 2, name: 'Privacy Policy', item: `${SITE}/privacy` },
  ],
};
---

<ContentLayout
  title="Privacy — alpha"
  description="Privacy policy for the alpha VS Code theme and its website. No data collection, no analytics, no third parties."
  canonical={`${SITE}/privacy`}
  activeNav="privacy"
  heading="Privacy"
  subtitle="Last updated: June 3, 2026"
  schema={schema}
>
  <div class="bg-card border border-white/[0.06] rounded-2xl p-6 my-8">
    <span class="inline-block bg-accent-green/[0.12] text-accent-green text-[13px] font-semibold px-3 py-1 rounded-full mb-3">Zero Data Collection</span>
    <p class="!text-text-strong !mb-0">The alpha extension contains no telemetry, no analytics, and no network code. The website is a static site with no trackers and no cookies.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>The extension</h2>
  <p>alpha is a VS Code color theme. It is a JSON declaration of editor colors and TextMate token rules. It has no executable code, no network access, and no way to collect or transmit data. Whatever your editor knows about your activity is governed by your VS Code and operating system settings — alpha sees none of it.</p>

  <h2>The website</h2>
  <p>This site (<strong>gokhangunduz.github.io/alpha</strong>) is a static Astro site hosted on GitHub Pages. It does not:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Set cookies</li>
    <li>Load analytics scripts</li>
    <li>Embed third-party trackers</li>
    <li>Collect form submissions (there are no forms)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>GitHub Pages itself may log standard request metadata (IP address, user agent, requested path) for security and operational purposes. That data is held by GitHub and is governed by <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-general-privacy-statement" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub's privacy statement</a>.</p>

  <h2>External links</h2>
  <p>This site links to the <a href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=gokhangunduz.alpha" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Visual Studio Marketplace</a> and to <a href="https://github.com/gokhangunduz/alpha" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>. Once you click through, you're subject to Microsoft's and GitHub's respective policies.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>If you have questions about privacy, reach out:</p>
  <p><strong>me@gokhangunduz.dev</strong></p>
</ContentLayout>
